input box similar as with splitwise:
<input
  type="text"
  placeholder="e.g. 12.34 or 12,34"
  pattern="^[0-9]+([.,][0-9]{1,2})?$"
  title="Please enter a number with up to 2 decimal places (dot or comma)."
  oninput="
    let v = this.value;

    // keep digits + dot/comma only
    v = v.replace(/[^0-9.,]/g, '');

    // allow only the first dot/comma as the decimal separator
    v = v.replace(/[.,](?=.*[.,])/g, '');

    // if a separator exists, keep only up to 2 digits after it
    v = v.replace(/^([0-9]+)([.,])(\d{0,2}).*$/, '$1$2$3');

    this.value = v;
  "
/>

* https://blog.jim-nielsen.com/2025/dont-forget-these-html-tags/

* Make second version with miso + servant + opaleye + sqlite + browser state => works offline
